    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.tsx`/`.ts` wizard implementation; carries ADR-012 / ADR-021 / ADR-022 / ADR-028 obligations; INV-5 enforcement; fixes a latent bug (G2) where CreateProjectWizard was NOT setting `sprk_containerid` at all.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches an independent wizard service file (CreateProjectWizard); file-disjoint from sibling wizard tasks 021, 023, 024, 025. All depend only on 020's shared-lib build.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    First verify the latent G2 gap: confirm that the current `CreateProjectWizard` does NOT set `sprk_containerid` on the create payload (spec.md §A1 records this as the assumed gap; spec FR-WIZ-02 explicitly calls it out). Then fix that gap AND add `sprk_searchindexname` from the user's BU. Both fields must end up populated on a newly-created Project. Honor INV-5.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke.UI.Components wizard implementer. React 18 + Fluent v9 + TypeScript. Familiar with CreateMatterWizard as the canonical reference and willing to surface the verification finding (G2 gap exists or doesn't) before applying the fix.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `CreateProjectWizard` produces a `sprk_project` record where BOTH `sprk_containerid` AND `sprk_searchindexname` are populated from the user's BU. The latent G2 bug (Project was not getting `sprk_containerid`) is fixed. INV-5 honored on both fields.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-WIZ-02 explicitly states CreateProjectWizard has a latent `sprk_containerid` gap — Project records were not getting their container ID set by the wizard, unlike Matter. This task fixes that AND adds `sprk_searchindexname`. The canonical pattern is `matterService.ts:216`: `entity['sprk_containerid'] = this._containerId;`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/CreateProjectWizard/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateProjectWizard/projectService.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateMatterWizard/matterService.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/EntityCreationService.ts</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Wizard logic lives in `@spaarke/ui-components` (projectService.ts). Do not put logic in the code-page directly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 + `tokens.*` only. No v8 imports, no hex / `var(--…)` / rgb literals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">Code page is React 18; shared lib must stay portable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Any BFF call uses `authenticatedFetch`. No new auth wiring.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md FR-WIZ-02">BOTH `sprk_containerid` AND `sprk_searchindexname` must be populated by the wizard.</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md INV-5">Never overwrite a pre-existing non-empty value on either field.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-ui-component-library.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-ui-v9.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-react-version-boundaries.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/auth.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Wizard sets BU-derived field on create payload" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateMatterWizard/matterService.ts">
        Line 216: `entity['sprk_containerid'] = this._containerId;` — copy this shape into projectService.ts for both `sprk_containerid` (gap fix) and `sprk_searchindexname` (new field).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">**Verify the G2 gap**: Read `projectService.ts` (and Project create payload code path) to confirm whether `sprk_containerid` is currently being set. Record the finding (yes/no) in the handoff file `notes/handoffs/022-project-wizard-g2-verification.md`. Spec assumption is that it is NOT being set — confirm or refute empirically.</step>
    <step order="2">Locate where the user's BU is loaded in `projectService.ts` (or where it should be — pattern from `matterService.ts:216`).</step>
    <step order="3">If G2 gap confirmed: add `sprk_containerid` cascade from BU, mirroring `matterService.ts:216` (`entity['sprk_containerid'] = this._containerId;`). INV-5: only set if payload value is currently null/empty.</step>
    <step order="4">Add `sprk_searchindexname` cascade from `businessunit.sprk_searchindexname` (extend the BU $select; do not issue a second roundtrip). INV-5 applied identically.</step>
    <step order="5">Run shared-lib build (`npm run build` in `Spaarke.UI.Components`); confirm clean compile.</step>
    <step order="6">Write/extend unit tests for `projectService` covering: (a) `sprk_containerid` cascade when empty; (b) `sprk_searchindexname` cascade when empty; (c) INV-5 for both — explicit payload values are preserved.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read projectService.ts + CreateProjectWizard code-page; cross-reference matterService.ts</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Add both `sprk_containerid` (gap fix) + `sprk_searchindexname` (new) to projectService.ts</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run `npm run build` in Spaarke.UI.Components</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateProjectWizard/projectService.ts (extended; G2 gap fixed)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1/notes/handoffs/022-project-wizard-g2-verification.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">FR-WIZ-02: After deploy + UAT (task 071), a Project created via the wizard has BOTH `sprk_containerid` AND `sprk_searchindexname` populated from the user's BU (MCP-verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">G2 latent gap fixed: `projectService.ts` now sets `sprk_containerid` (it did not before; verification documented in handoff).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">INV-5: Unit tests confirm pre-set values on either field are preserved through the cascade.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` in `Spaarke.UI.Components` is clean.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    **G2 LATENT GAP NOTICE**: This task explicitly fixes a pre-existing bug where `CreateProjectWizard` was not setting `sprk_containerid` at all (per spec.md FR-WIZ-02 and §A1 assumption). The verification in Step 1 may surface that the gap is partially closed already (e.g. set elsewhere) — record the finding either way. If the gap turns out to NOT exist, narrow the task to just the `sprk_searchindexname` add and update the handoff file.

    Tasks 023, 024, 025 (Invoice, WorkAssignment, Event) have similar "verify-first-then-fix-if-needed" semantics for `sprk_containerid` — different from the Matter case where the field is already wired.
  </notes>

